<seg id="750">& dot; -algorithm, the standard for directed graphs. it produces hierarchical or layered representations of directed graphs. the algorithm puts the edges in the same direction (from top to bottom or from left to right) and then tries to produce as short edges and as few edge overlaps as possible.</seg>
<seg id="751">The & neato; -algorithm is the standard for unerized graphs. it produces representations in accordance with the springy model. the Kamada-Kawai algorithm is used, which is synonymous with statistical multi-dimensional scaling.</seg>
<seg id="752">The & fdp; -algorithm generates a springspringmodel layout for ungerized graphs. it uses the Fruckerman-Reingold heuristics, and includes a multi-grid trigger for the treatment of large and clustered graphs.</seg>
<seg id="753">The & circo; -algorithm calculates the vertices circular in accordance with the description of Six and tollis, 1999, and Kauffman and Wiese, 2002. it is useful for certain diagrams of multiple cyclical structures.</seg>
